# Pepper ROS Noetic Setup Guide

This repository contains everything needed to run the **Pepper ROS** Gazebo simulation in Docker. No external images required — builds from scratch on Ubuntu 20.04.

## 1. Build the image
docker build -t pepper .

Note: First build will take a while (ROS Noetic + Pepper packages + gzweb).

## 2. Run the container

### Enable GUI support (Linux with X11)
xhost +local:docker

### Launch Container
docker run -it --rm \
    -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY \
    -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix \
    -p 8080:8080 \
    pepper

## 3. In the container

### Launch the simulation (with GUI)
roslaunch pepper_gazebo_plugin pepper_gazebo_plugin_Y20.launch

### Launch the simulation (headless, view via http://localhost:8080)
roslaunch pepper_gazebo_plugin pepper_gazebo_plugin_Y20.launch gui:=false
